28/*
29 notes: This implementation is rather basic. There are several implementation
30 issues to be sorted out for full compliance and error resilience.
31 Some examples are given below (nasm syntax).
32
33 1) section placement
34 Mach-O requires BSS sections to be placed last in object files. This
35 has to be done manually.
36 Example:
37
38 section .text
39 mov rax,[qword foo]
40 section .data
41 dw 0
42 section .bss
43 foo dw 0
44
45 2) addressing issues
46
47 2.1) symbol relative relocation (i.e. mov eax,[foo wrt bar])
48 Not implemented yet.
49
50 2.2) data referencing in 64 bit mode
51 While ELF allows 32 bit absolute relocations in 64 bit mode, Mach-O
52 does not. Therefore code like
53 lea rbx,[_foo] ;48 8d 1c 25 00 00 00 00
54 mov rcx,[_bar] ;48 8b 0c 25 00 00 00 00
55 with a 32 bit address field cannot be relocated into an address >= 0x100000000 (OSX actually
56 uses that).
57
58 Actually, the only register where a 64 bit displacement is allowed in x86-64, is rax
59 as in the example 1).
60
61 A plausible workaround is either classic PIC (like in C), which is in turn
62 not implemented in this object format. The recommended was is PC relative
63 code (called RIP-relative in x86-64). So instead of the lines above, just write:
64 lea rbx,[_foo wrt rip]
65 mov rcx,[_bar wrt rip]
66
67 2.3) section/data alignment
68 Normally, you specify sections with a specific alignment
69 and get your data layed out as desired. Unfortunately, the
70 linker in MacOS X seems to ignore the section alignment requests.
71 The workaround is an explicit alignment at the end of the text section.
72
73 section .text
74 movdqa xmm0,[_foo wrt rip]
75
76 align 16
77 section .data align=16
78 _foo dw 32,32,32,32,32,32,32,32
79
80 FIXME: perform that operation implicitly!
81
82 2.4) cross section symbol differences unsupported in current implementation
83 [extern foo]
84 [extern bar]
85 section .data
86 dq bar-foo
87
88 Will currently produce an error though the necessary means are provided
89 by the Mach-O specification.
90
91*/

236typedef struct macho_reloc {
237 yasm_reloc reloc;
238 int pcrel;
239 int length;
240 int ext;
241 enum reloc_type_x86_64 {
242 /* x86 relocations */
243 GENERIC_RELOC_VANILLA = 0, /* generic relocation */
244 GENERIC_RELOC_PAIR = 1, /* Only follows a GENERIC_RELOC_SECTDIFF */
245 GENERIC_RELOC_SECTDIFF = 2,
246 GENERIC_RELOC_PB_LA_PTR = 3, /* prebound lazy pointer */
247 GENERIC_RELOC_LOCAL_SECTDIFF = 4,
248
249 /* x86-64 relocations */
250 X86_64_RELOC_UNSIGNED = 0, /* for absolute addresses */
251 X86_64_RELOC_SIGNED = 1, /* for signed 32-bit displacement */
252 X86_64_RELOC_BRANCH = 2, /* a CALL/JMP insn with 32-bit disp */
253 X86_64_RELOC_GOT_LOAD = 3, /* a MOVQ load of a GOT entry */
254 X86_64_RELOC_GOT = 4, /* other GOT references */
255 X86_64_RELOC_SUBTRACTOR = 5, /* must be followed by a X86_64_RELOC_UNSIGNED */
256 X86_64_RELOC_SIGNED_1 = 6, /* signed 32-bit disp, -1 addend */
257 X86_64_RELOC_SIGNED_2 = 7, /* signed 32-bit disp, -2 addend */
258 X86_64_RELOC_SIGNED_4 = 8 /* signed 32-bit disp, -4 addend */
259 } type;
260} macho_reloc;

340static yasm_objfmt *
341macho_objfmt_create_common(yasm_object *object, yasm_objfmt_module *module,
342 int bits_pref)
343{
344 yasm_objfmt_macho *objfmt_macho = yasm_xmalloc(sizeof(yasm_objfmt_macho));
345
346 objfmt_macho->objfmt.module = module;
347
348 /* Only support x86 arch for now */
349 if (yasm__strcasecmp(yasm_arch_keyword(object->arch), "x86") != 0) {
350 yasm_xfree(objfmt_macho);
351 return NULL;
352 }
353
354 /* Support x86 and amd64 machines of x86 arch */
355 if (yasm__strcasecmp(yasm_arch_get_machine(object->arch), "x86") == 0 &&
356 (bits_pref == 0 || bits_pref == 32)) {
357 objfmt_macho->bits = 32;
358 objfmt_macho->gotpcrel_sym = NULL;
359 } else if (yasm__strcasecmp(yasm_arch_get_machine(object->arch),
360 "amd64") == 0 &&
361 (bits_pref == 0 || bits_pref == 64)) {
362 objfmt_macho->bits = 64;
363 /* FIXME: misuse of NULL bytecode */
364 objfmt_macho->gotpcrel_sym =
365 yasm_symtab_define_label(object->symtab, "..gotpcrel", NULL, 0, 0);
366 } else {
367 yasm_xfree(objfmt_macho);
368 return NULL;
369 }
370
371 objfmt_macho->parse_scnum = 0; /* section numbering starts at 0 */
372 return (yasm_objfmt *)objfmt_macho;
373}
374
375static yasm_objfmt *
376macho_objfmt_create(yasm_object *object)
377{
378 yasm_objfmt *objfmt;
379 yasm_objfmt_macho *objfmt_macho;
380
381 objfmt = macho_objfmt_create_common(object, &yasm_macho_LTX_objfmt, 0);
382 if (objfmt) {
383 objfmt_macho = (yasm_objfmt_macho *)objfmt;
384 /* Figure out which bitness of object format to use */
385 if (objfmt_macho->bits == 32)
386 objfmt_macho->objfmt.module = &yasm_macho32_LTX_objfmt;
387 else if (objfmt_macho->bits == 64)
388 objfmt_macho->objfmt.module = &yasm_macho64_LTX_objfmt;
389 }
390 return objfmt;
391}

405static int
406macho_objfmt_output_value(yasm_value *value, unsigned char *buf,
407 unsigned int destsize, unsigned long offset,
408 yasm_bytecode *bc, int warn, /*@null@*/ void *d)
409{
410 /*@null@*/ macho_objfmt_output_info *info = (macho_objfmt_output_info *)d;
411 yasm_objfmt_macho *objfmt_macho;
412 /*@dependent@*/ /*@null@*/ yasm_intnum *intn;
413 unsigned long intn_minus = 0, intn_plus = 0;
414 int retval;
415 unsigned int valsize = value->size;
416 macho_reloc *reloc = NULL;
417
418 assert(info != NULL);
419 objfmt_macho = info->objfmt_macho;
420
421 if (value->abs)
422 value->abs = yasm_expr_simplify(value->abs, 1);
423
424 /* Try to output constant and PC-relative section-local first.
425 * Note this does NOT output any value with a SEG, WRT, external,
426 * cross-section, or non-PC-relative reference (those are handled below).
427 */
428 switch (yasm_value_output_basic(value, buf, destsize, bc, warn,
429 info->object->arch)) {
430 case -1:
431 return 1;
432 case 0:
433 break;
434 default:
435 return 0;
436 }
437
438 if (value->section_rel) {
439 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_TOO_COMPLEX,
440 N_("macho: relocation too complex for current implementation"));
441 return 1;
442 }
443
444 if (value->rel) {
445 yasm_sym_vis vis = yasm_symrec_get_visibility(value->rel);
446
447 reloc = yasm_xcalloc(sizeof(macho_reloc), 1);
448 reloc->reloc.addr = yasm_intnum_create_uint(bc->offset + offset);
449 reloc->reloc.sym = value->rel;
450 switch (valsize) {
451 case 64:
452 reloc->length = 3;
453 break;
454 case 32:
455 reloc->length = 2;
456 break;
457 case 16:
458 reloc->length = 1;
459 break;
460 case 8:
461 reloc->length = 0;
462 break;
463 default:
464 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_TOO_COMPLEX,
465 N_("macho: relocation size unsupported"));
466 yasm_xfree(reloc);
467 return 1;
468 }
469 reloc->pcrel = 0;
470 reloc->ext = 0;
471 reloc->type = GENERIC_RELOC_VANILLA;
472 /* R_ABS */
473
474 if (value->rshift > 0) {
475 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_TOO_COMPLEX,
476 N_("macho: shifted relocations not supported"));
477 yasm_xfree(reloc);
478 return 1;
479 }
480
481 if (value->seg_of) {
482 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_TOO_COMPLEX,
483 N_("macho: SEG not supported"));
484 yasm_xfree(reloc);
485 return 1;
486 }
487
488 if (value->curpos_rel && objfmt_macho->gotpcrel_sym &&
489 value->wrt == objfmt_macho->gotpcrel_sym) {
490 reloc->type = X86_64_RELOC_GOT;
491 value->wrt = NULL;
492 } else if (value->wrt) {
493 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_TOO_COMPLEX,
494 N_("macho: invalid WRT"));
495 yasm_xfree(reloc);
496 return 1;
497 }
498
499 if (value->curpos_rel) {
500 reloc->pcrel = 1;
501 if (!info->is_64) {
502 /* Adjust to start of section, so subtract out the bytecode
503 * offset.
504 */
505 intn_minus = bc->offset;
506 } else {
507 /* Add in the offset plus value size to end up with 0. */
508 intn_plus = offset+destsize;
509 if (reloc->type == X86_64_RELOC_GOT) {
510 /* XXX: This is a hack */
511 if (offset >= 2 && buf[-2] == 0x8B)
512 reloc->type = X86_64_RELOC_GOT_LOAD;
513 } else if (value->jump_target)
514 reloc->type = X86_64_RELOC_BRANCH;
515 else
516 reloc->type = X86_64_RELOC_SIGNED;
517 }
518 } else if (info->is_64) {
519 if (valsize == 32) {
520 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_NOT_CONSTANT,
521 N_("macho: sorry, cannot apply 32 bit absolute relocations in 64 bit mode, consider \"[_symbol wrt rip]\" for mem access, \"qword\" and \"dq _foo\" for pointers."));
522 return 1;
523 }
524 reloc->type = X86_64_RELOC_UNSIGNED;
525 }
526
527 /* It seems that x86-64 objects need to have all extern relocs? */
528 if (info->is_64)
529 reloc->ext = 1;
530
531 if ((vis & YASM_SYM_EXTERN) || (vis & YASM_SYM_COMMON)) {
532 reloc->ext = 1;
533 info->msd->extreloc = 1; /* section has external relocations */
534 } else if (!info->is_64) {
535 /*@dependent@*/ /*@null@*/ yasm_bytecode *sym_precbc;
536
537 /* Local symbols need valued to their actual address */
538 if (yasm_symrec_get_label(value->rel, &sym_precbc)) {
539 yasm_section *sym_sect = yasm_bc_get_section(sym_precbc);
540 /*@null@*/ macho_section_data *msd;
541 msd = yasm_section_get_data(sym_sect, &macho_section_data_cb);
542 assert(msd != NULL);
543 intn_plus += msd->vmoff + yasm_bc_next_offset(sym_precbc);
544 }
545 }
546
547 info->msd->nreloc++;
548 /*printf("reloc %s type %d ",yasm_symrec_get_name(reloc->reloc.sym),reloc->type);*/
549 yasm_section_add_reloc(info->sect, (yasm_reloc *)reloc, yasm_xfree);
550 }
551
552 if (intn_minus <= intn_plus)
553 intn = yasm_intnum_create_uint(intn_plus-intn_minus);
554 else {
555 intn = yasm_intnum_create_uint(intn_minus-intn_plus);
556 yasm_intnum_calc(intn, YASM_EXPR_NEG, NULL);
557 }
558
559 if (value->abs) {
560 yasm_intnum *intn2 = yasm_expr_get_intnum(&value->abs, 0);
561
562 if (!intn2) {
563 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_TOO_COMPLEX,
564 N_("macho: relocation too complex"));
565 yasm_intnum_destroy(intn);
566 return 1;
567 }
568 yasm_intnum_calc(intn, YASM_EXPR_ADD, intn2);
569 }
570
571 retval = yasm_arch_intnum_tobytes(info->object->arch, intn, buf, destsize,
572 valsize, 0, bc, warn);
573 /*printf("val %ld\n",yasm_intnum_get_int(intn));*/
574 yasm_intnum_destroy(intn);
575 return retval;
576}

578static int
579macho_objfmt_output_bytecode(yasm_bytecode *bc, /*@null@*/ void *d)
580{
581 /*@null@*/ macho_objfmt_output_info *info = (macho_objfmt_output_info *)d;
582 /*@null@*/ /*@only@*/ unsigned char *bigbuf;
583 unsigned long size = REGULAR_OUTBUF_SIZE;
584 int gap;
585
586 assert(info != NULL);
587
588 bigbuf = yasm_bc_tobytes(bc, info->buf, &size, &gap, info,
589 macho_objfmt_output_value, NULL);
590
591 /* Don't bother doing anything else if size ended up being 0. */
592 if (size == 0) {
593 if (bigbuf)
594 yasm_xfree(bigbuf);
595 return 0;
596 }
597
598 /* Warn that gaps are converted to 0 and write out the 0's. */
599 if (gap) {
600 unsigned long left;
601
602 yasm_warn_set(YASM_WARN_UNINIT_CONTENTS,
603 N_("uninitialized space: zeroing"));
604 /* Write out in chunks */
605 memset(info->buf, 0, REGULAR_OUTBUF_SIZE);
606 left = size;
607 while (left > REGULAR_OUTBUF_SIZE) {
608 fwrite(info->buf, REGULAR_OUTBUF_SIZE, 1, info->f);
609 left -= REGULAR_OUTBUF_SIZE;
610 }
611 fwrite(info->buf, left, 1, info->f);
612 } else {
613 /* Output buf (or bigbuf if non-NULL) to file */
614 fwrite(bigbuf ? bigbuf : info->buf, (size_t) size, 1, info->f);
615 }
616
617 /* If bigbuf was allocated, free it */
618 if (bigbuf)
619 yasm_xfree(bigbuf);
620
621 return 0;
622}

624static int
625macho_objfmt_output_section(yasm_section *sect, /*@null@ */ void *d)
626{
627 /*@null@ */ macho_objfmt_output_info *info =
628 (macho_objfmt_output_info *) d;
629 /*@dependent@ *//*@null@ */ macho_section_data *msd;
630
631 assert(info != NULL);
632 msd = yasm_section_get_data(sect, &macho_section_data_cb);
633 assert(msd != NULL);
634
635 if (!(msd->flags & S_ZEROFILL)) {
636 /* Output non-BSS sections */
637 info->sect = sect;
638 info->msd = msd;
639 yasm_section_bcs_traverse(sect, info->errwarns, info,
640 macho_objfmt_output_bytecode);
641 }
642 return 0;
643}

645static int
646macho_objfmt_output_relocs(yasm_section *sect, /*@null@*/ void *d)
647{
648 /*@null@*/ macho_objfmt_output_info *info = (macho_objfmt_output_info *)d;
649 /*@dependent@*/ /*@null@*/ macho_section_data *msd;
650 macho_reloc *reloc;
651
652 reloc = (macho_reloc *)yasm_section_relocs_first(sect);
653 while (reloc) {
654 unsigned char *localbuf = info->buf;
655 /*@null@*/ macho_symrec_data *xsymd;
656 unsigned long symnum;
657
658 xsymd = yasm_symrec_get_data(reloc->reloc.sym, &macho_symrec_data_cb);
659 yasm_intnum_get_sized(reloc->reloc.addr, localbuf, 4, 32, 0, 0, 0);
660 localbuf += 4; /* address of relocation */
661
662 if (reloc->ext)
663 symnum = xsymd->index;
664 else {
665 /* find section where the symbol relates to */
666 /*@dependent@*/ /*@null@*/ yasm_section *dsect;
667 /*@dependent@*/ /*@null@*/ yasm_bytecode *precbc;
668 symnum = 0; /* default to absolute */
669 if (yasm_symrec_get_label(reloc->reloc.sym, &precbc) &&
670 (dsect = yasm_bc_get_section(precbc)) &&
671 (msd = yasm_section_get_data(dsect, &macho_section_data_cb)))
672 symnum = msd->scnum+1;
673 }
674 YASM_WRITE_32_L(localbuf,
675 (symnum & 0x00ffffff) |
676 (((unsigned long)reloc->pcrel & 1) << 24) |
677 (((unsigned long)reloc->length & 3) << 25) |
678 (((unsigned long)reloc->ext & 1) << 27) |
679 (((unsigned long)reloc->type & 0xf) << 28));
680 fwrite(info->buf, 8, 1, info->f);
681 reloc = (macho_reloc *)yasm_section_reloc_next((yasm_reloc *)reloc);
682 }
683
684 return 0;
685}
686
687static int
688exp2_to_bits(unsigned long val)
689{
690 int ret = 0;
691
692 while (val) {
693 val >>= 1;
694 ret++;
695 }
696 ret = (ret > 0) ? ret - 1 : 0;
697
698 return ret;
699}

701static int
702macho_objfmt_is_section_label(yasm_symrec *sym)
703{
704 /*@dependent@*/ /*@null@*/ yasm_section *sect;
705 /*@dependent@*/ /*@null@*/ yasm_bytecode *precbc;
706
707 /* Look at symrec for value/scnum/etc. */
708 if (yasm_symrec_get_label(sym, &precbc)) {
709 if (precbc)
710 sect = yasm_bc_get_section(precbc);
711 else
712 sect = NULL;
713 /* it's a label: get value and offset.
714 * If there is not a section, leave as debugging symbol.
715 */
716 if (sect) {
717 /*@dependent@*/ /*@null@*/ macho_section_data *msd;
718
719 msd = yasm_section_get_data(sect, &macho_section_data_cb);
720 if (msd) {
721 if (msd->sym == sym)
722 return 1; /* don't store section names */
723 }
724 }
725 }
726 return 0;
727}

729static int
730macho_objfmt_output_secthead(yasm_section *sect, /*@null@*/ void *d)
731{
732 /*@null@*/ macho_objfmt_output_info *info = (macho_objfmt_output_info *)d;
733 /*@dependent@*/ /*@null@*/ macho_section_data *msd;
734 unsigned char *localbuf;
735
736 assert(info != NULL);
737 msd = yasm_section_get_data(sect, &macho_section_data_cb);
738 assert(msd != NULL);
739
740 localbuf = info->buf;
741
742 memset(localbuf, 0, 16);
743 strncpy((char *)localbuf, msd->sectname, 16);
744 localbuf += 16;
745 memset(localbuf, 0, 16);
746 strncpy((char *)localbuf, msd->segname, 16);
747 localbuf += 16;
748 /* section address, size depend on 32/64 bit mode */
749 YASM_WRITE_32_L(localbuf, msd->vmoff); /* address in memory */
750 if (info->is_64)
751 YASM_WRITE_32_L(localbuf, 0); /* 64-bit mode: upper 32 bits = 0 */
752 YASM_WRITE_32_L(localbuf, msd->size); /* size in memory */
753 if (info->is_64)
754 YASM_WRITE_32_L(localbuf, 0); /* 64-bit mode: upper 32 bits = 0 */
755
756 /* offset,align,reloff,nreloc,flags,reserved1,reserved2 are 32 bit */
757 if ((msd->flags & SECTION_TYPE) != S_ZEROFILL) {
758 YASM_WRITE_32_L(localbuf, msd->offset);
759 YASM_WRITE_32_L(localbuf, exp2_to_bits(yasm_section_get_align(sect)));
760 if (msd->nreloc) {
761 msd->flags |= S_ATTR_LOC_RELOC;
762 if (msd->extreloc)
763 msd->flags |= S_ATTR_EXT_RELOC;
764 YASM_WRITE_32_L(localbuf,
765 align32((long)(info->rel_base + info->s_reloff)));
766 YASM_WRITE_32_L(localbuf, msd->nreloc); /* nreloc */
767 } else {
768 YASM_WRITE_32_L(localbuf, 0);
769 YASM_WRITE_32_L(localbuf, 0);
770 }
771
772 info->s_reloff += msd->nreloc * MACHO_RELINFO_SIZE; /* nreloc */
773 } else {
774 YASM_WRITE_32_L(localbuf, 0); /* these are zero in BSS */
775 YASM_WRITE_32_L(localbuf, 0);
776 YASM_WRITE_32_L(localbuf, 0);
777 YASM_WRITE_32_L(localbuf, 0);
778 }
779
780 YASM_WRITE_32_L(localbuf, msd->flags); /* flags */
781 YASM_WRITE_32_L(localbuf, 0); /* reserved 1 */
782 YASM_WRITE_32_L(localbuf, 0); /* reserved 2 */
783
784 if (info->is_64)
785 fwrite(info->buf, MACHO_SECTCMD64_SIZE, 1, info->f);
786 else
787 fwrite(info->buf, MACHO_SECTCMD_SIZE, 1, info->f);
788
789 return 0;
790}

793static int
794macho_objfmt_count_sym(yasm_symrec *sym, /*@null@*/ void *d)
795{
796 /*@null@*/ macho_objfmt_output_info *info = (macho_objfmt_output_info *)d;
797 /*@only@*/ char *name;
798 yasm_sym_vis vis = yasm_symrec_get_visibility(sym);
799
800 assert(info != NULL);
801 if (info->all_syms ||
802 vis & (YASM_SYM_GLOBAL | YASM_SYM_COMMON | YASM_SYM_EXTERN)) {
803 if (0 == macho_objfmt_is_section_label(sym)) {
804 /* Save index in symrec data */
805 macho_symrec_data *sym_data =
806 yasm_symrec_get_data(sym, &macho_symrec_data_cb);
807 if (!sym_data) {
808 sym_data = yasm_xcalloc(sizeof(macho_symrec_data), 1);
809 yasm_symrec_add_data(sym, &macho_symrec_data_cb, sym_data);
810 }
811 sym_data->index = info->symindex;
812 info->symindex++;
813
814 name = yasm_symrec_get_global_name(sym, info->object);
815 /*printf("%s\n",name); */
816 /* name length + delimiter */
817 sym_data->length = (unsigned long)strlen(name) + 1;
818 info->strlength += sym_data->length;
819 info->indx++;
820 yasm_xfree(name);
821 }
822 }
823 return 0;
824}

826
827static int
828macho_objfmt_output_symtable(yasm_symrec *sym, /*@null@*/ void *d)
829{
830 /*@null@*/ macho_objfmt_output_info *info = (macho_objfmt_output_info *)d;
831 yasm_sym_vis vis = yasm_symrec_get_visibility(sym);
832
833 assert(info != NULL);
834
835 if (info->all_syms ||
836 vis & (YASM_SYM_GLOBAL | YASM_SYM_COMMON | YASM_SYM_EXTERN)) {
837 const yasm_expr *equ_val;
838 const yasm_intnum *intn;
839 unsigned long value = 0;
840 long scnum = -3; /* -3 = debugging symbol */
841 /*@dependent@*/ /*@null@*/ yasm_section *sect;
842 /*@dependent@*/ /*@null@*/ yasm_bytecode *precbc;
843 unsigned char *localbuf;
844 yasm_intnum *val;
845 unsigned int long_int_bytes = (info->is_64) ? 8 : 4;
846 unsigned int n_type = 0, n_sect = 0, n_desc = 0;
847 macho_symrec_data *symd;
848
849 val = yasm_intnum_create_uint(0);
850
851 symd = yasm_symrec_get_data(sym, &macho_symrec_data_cb);
852
853 /* Look at symrec for value/scnum/etc. */
854 if (yasm_symrec_get_label(sym, &precbc)) {
855 if (precbc)
856 sect = yasm_bc_get_section(precbc);
857 else
858 sect = NULL;
859 /* it's a label: get value and offset.
860 * If there is not a section, leave as debugging symbol.
861 */
862 if (sect) {
863 /*@dependent@*/ /*@null@*/ macho_section_data *msd;
864
865 msd = yasm_section_get_data(sect, &macho_section_data_cb);
866 if (msd) {
867 if (msd->sym == sym) {
868 /* don't store section names */
869 yasm_intnum_destroy(val);
870 return 0;
871 }
872 scnum = msd->scnum;
873 n_type = N_SECT;
874 } else
875 yasm_internal_error(N_("didn't understand section"));
876 if (precbc)
877 value += yasm_bc_next_offset(precbc);
878 /* all values are subject to correction: base offset is first
879 * raw section, therefore add section offset
880 */
881 if (msd)
882 value += msd->vmoff;
883 yasm_intnum_set_uint(val, value);
884 /*printf("%s offset %lx\n",name,value);*/
885 }
886 } else if ((equ_val = yasm_symrec_get_equ(sym))) {
887 yasm_expr *equ_val_copy = yasm_expr_copy(equ_val);
888
889 intn = yasm_expr_get_intnum(&equ_val_copy, 1);
890 if (!intn) {
891 if (vis & YASM_SYM_GLOBAL) {
892 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_NOT_CONSTANT,
893 N_("global EQU value not an integer expression"));
894 yasm_errwarn_propagate(info->errwarns, equ_val->line);
895 }
896 } else
897 value = yasm_intnum_get_uint(intn);
898 yasm_expr_destroy(equ_val_copy);
899 yasm_intnum_set_uint(val, value);
900 n_type = N_ABS;
901 scnum = -2; /* -2 = absolute symbol */
902 }
903
904 if (vis & YASM_SYM_EXTERN) {
905 n_type = N_EXT;
906 scnum = -1;
907 /*n_desc = REFERENCE_FLAG_UNDEFINED_LAZY; * FIXME: see definition of REFERENCE_FLAG_* above */
908 } else if (vis & YASM_SYM_COMMON) {
909 yasm_expr **csize = yasm_symrec_get_common_size(sym);
910 n_type = N_UNDF | N_EXT;
911 if (csize) {
912 intn = yasm_expr_get_intnum(csize, 1);
913 if (!intn) {
914 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_NOT_CONSTANT,
915 N_("COMMON data size not an integer expression"));
916 yasm_errwarn_propagate(info->errwarns, (*csize)->line);
917 } else
918 yasm_intnum_set_uint(val, yasm_intnum_get_uint(intn));
919 }
920 /*printf("common symbol %s val %lu\n", name, yasm_intnum_get_uint(val));*/
921 } else if (vis & YASM_SYM_GLOBAL) {
922 yasm_valparamhead *valparams =
923 yasm_symrec_get_objext_valparams(sym);
924
925 struct macho_global_data {
926 unsigned long flag; /* N_PEXT */
927 } data;
928
929 data.flag = 0;
930
931 if (valparams) {
932 static const yasm_dir_help help[] = {
933 { "private_extern", 0, yasm_dir_helper_flag_set,
934 offsetof(struct macho_global_data, flag), N_PEXT },
935 };
936 yasm_dir_helper(sym, yasm_vps_first(valparams),
937 yasm_symrec_get_decl_line(sym), help, NELEMS(help),
938 &data, yasm_dir_helper_valparam_warn);
939 }
940
941 n_type |= N_EXT | data.flag;
942 }
943
944 localbuf = info->buf;
945 YASM_WRITE_32_L(localbuf, info->indx); /* offset in string table */
946 YASM_WRITE_8(localbuf, n_type); /* type of symbol entry */
947 n_sect = (scnum >= 0) ? scnum + 1 : NO_SECT;
948 YASM_WRITE_8(localbuf, n_sect); /* referring section where symbol is found */
949 YASM_WRITE_16_L(localbuf, n_desc); /* extra description */
950 yasm_intnum_get_sized(val, localbuf, long_int_bytes, ((long_int_bytes) << 3), 0, 0, 0); /* value/argument */
951 localbuf += long_int_bytes;
952 if (symd)
953 symd->value = val;
954 else
955 yasm_intnum_destroy(val);
956
957 info->indx += symd->length;
958
959 fwrite(info->buf, 8 + long_int_bytes, 1, info->f);
960 }
961
962 return 0;
963}

988static int
989macho_objfmt_calc_sectsize(yasm_section *sect, /*@null@ */ void *d)
990{
991 /*@null@ */ macho_objfmt_output_info *info =
992 (macho_objfmt_output_info *) d;
993 /*@dependent@ *//*@null@ */ macho_section_data *msd;
994 unsigned long align;
995
996 assert(info != NULL);
997 msd = yasm_section_get_data(sect, &macho_section_data_cb);
998 assert(msd != NULL);
999
1000 msd->size = yasm_bc_next_offset(yasm_section_bcs_last(sect));
1001 if (!(msd->flags & S_ZEROFILL)) {
1002 msd->offset = info->offset;
1003 info->offset += msd->size;
1004 info->filesize += msd->size;
1005 }
1006
1007 /* accumulate size in memory */
1008 msd->vmoff = info->vmsize;
1009 info->vmsize += msd->size;
1010
1011 /* align both start and end of section */
1012 align = yasm_section_get_align(sect);
1013 if (align != 0) {
1014 unsigned long delta = msd->vmoff % align;
1015 if (delta > 0) {
1016 msd->vmoff += align - delta;
1017 info->vmsize += align - delta;
1018 }
1019 }
1020
1021 return 0;
1022}
1023
1024/* write object */
1025static void
1026macho_objfmt_output(yasm_object *object, FILE *f, int all_syms,
1027 yasm_errwarns *errwarns)
1028{
1029 yasm_objfmt_macho *objfmt_macho = (yasm_objfmt_macho *)object->objfmt;
1030 macho_objfmt_output_info info;
1031 unsigned char *localbuf;
1032 unsigned long symtab_count = 0;
1033 unsigned long headsize;
1034 unsigned int macho_segcmdsize, macho_sectcmdsize, macho_nlistsize;
1035 unsigned int macho_segcmd;
1036 unsigned int head_ncmds, head_sizeofcmds;
1037 unsigned long fileoffset, fileoff_sections;
1038 yasm_intnum *val;
1039 unsigned long long_int_bytes;
1040 const char pad_data[3] = "\0\0\0";
1041
1042 info.object = object;
1043 info.objfmt_macho = objfmt_macho;
1044 info.errwarns = errwarns;
1045 info.f = f;
1046 info.buf = yasm_xmalloc(REGULAR_OUTBUF_SIZE);
1047
1048 if (objfmt_macho->parse_scnum == 0) {
1049 yasm_internal_error(N_("no sections defined"));
1050 /*@notreached@*/
1051 return;
1052 }
1053
1054 val = yasm_intnum_create_uint(0);
1055
1056 /*
1057 * MACH-O Header, Seg CMD, Sect CMDs, Sym Tab, Reloc Data
1058 */
1059 info.is_64 = (objfmt_macho->bits == 32) ? 0 : 1;
1060 if (info.is_64) {
1061 /* this works only when SYMBOLS and SECTIONS present */
1062 headsize =
1063 MACHO_HEADER64_SIZE + MACHO_SEGCMD64_SIZE +
1064 (MACHO_SECTCMD64_SIZE * (objfmt_macho->parse_scnum)) +
1065 MACHO_SYMCMD_SIZE;
1066 macho_segcmd = LC_SEGMENT_64;
1067 macho_segcmdsize = MACHO_SEGCMD64_SIZE;
1068 macho_sectcmdsize = MACHO_SECTCMD64_SIZE;
1069 macho_nlistsize = MACHO_NLIST64_SIZE;
1070 long_int_bytes = 8;
1071 } else {
1072 headsize =
1073 MACHO_HEADER_SIZE + MACHO_SEGCMD_SIZE +
1074 (MACHO_SECTCMD_SIZE * (objfmt_macho->parse_scnum)) +
1075 MACHO_SYMCMD_SIZE;
1076 macho_segcmd = LC_SEGMENT;
1077 macho_segcmdsize = MACHO_SEGCMD_SIZE;
1078 macho_sectcmdsize = MACHO_SECTCMD_SIZE;
1079 macho_nlistsize = MACHO_NLIST_SIZE;
1080 long_int_bytes = 4;
1081 }
1082
1083 /* Get number of symbols */
1084 info.symindex = 0;
1085 info.indx = 0;
1086 info.strlength = 1; /* string table starts with a zero byte */
1087 info.all_syms = all_syms || info.is_64;
1088 /*info.all_syms = 1; * force all syms into symbol table */
1089 yasm_symtab_traverse(object->symtab, &info, macho_objfmt_count_sym);
1090 symtab_count = info.indx;
1091
1092 /* write raw section data first */
1093 if (fseek(f, (long)headsize, SEEK_SET) < 0) {
1094 yasm__fatal(N_("could not seek on output file"));
1095 /*@notreached@ */
1096 return;
1097 }
1098
1099 /* get size of sections in memory (including BSS) and size of sections
1100 * in file (without BSS)
1101 */
1102 info.vmsize = 0;
1103 info.filesize = 0;
1104 info.offset = headsize;
1105 yasm_object_sections_traverse(object, &info, macho_objfmt_calc_sectsize);
1106
1107 /* output sections to file */
1108 yasm_object_sections_traverse(object, &info, macho_objfmt_output_section);
1109
1110 fileoff_sections = ftell(f);
1111
1112 /* Write headers */
1113 if (fseek(f, 0, SEEK_SET) < 0) {
1114 yasm__fatal(N_("could not seek on output file"));
1115 /*@notreached@*/
1116 return;
1117 }
1118
1119 localbuf = info.buf;
1120
1121 /* header size is common to 32 bit and 64 bit variants */
1122 if (info.is_64) {
1123 YASM_WRITE_32_L(localbuf, MH_MAGIC_64); /* magic number */
1124 /* i386 64-bit ABI */
1125 YASM_WRITE_32_L(localbuf, CPU_ARCH_ABI64 | CPU_TYPE_I386);
1126 } else {
1127 YASM_WRITE_32_L(localbuf, MH_MAGIC); /* magic number */
1128 YASM_WRITE_32_L(localbuf, CPU_TYPE_I386); /* i386 32-bit ABI */
1129 }
1130 /* i386 all cpu subtype compatible */
1131 YASM_WRITE_32_L(localbuf, CPU_SUBTYPE_I386_ALL);
1132 YASM_WRITE_32_L(localbuf, MH_OBJECT); /* MACH file type */
1133
1134 /* calculate number of commands and their size, put to stream */
1135 head_ncmds = 0;
1136 head_sizeofcmds = 0;
1137 if (objfmt_macho->parse_scnum > 0) {
1138 head_ncmds++;
1139 head_sizeofcmds +=
1140 macho_segcmdsize + macho_sectcmdsize * objfmt_macho->parse_scnum;
1141 }
1142 if (symtab_count > 0) {
1143 head_ncmds++;
1144 head_sizeofcmds += MACHO_SYMCMD_SIZE;
1145 }
1146
1147 YASM_WRITE_32_L(localbuf, head_ncmds);
1148 YASM_WRITE_32_L(localbuf, head_sizeofcmds);
1149 YASM_WRITE_32_L(localbuf, 0); /* no flags (yet) */
1150 if (info.is_64) {
1151 YASM_WRITE_32_L(localbuf, 0); /* reserved in 64 bit */
1152 fileoffset = MACHO_HEADER64_SIZE + head_sizeofcmds;
1153 } else {
1154 /* initial offset to first section */
1155 fileoffset = MACHO_HEADER_SIZE + head_sizeofcmds;
1156 }
1157
1158 /* --------------- write segment header command ---------------- */
1159 YASM_WRITE_32_L(localbuf, macho_segcmd); /* command LC_SEGMENT */
1160 /* size of load command including section load commands */
1161 YASM_WRITE_32_L(localbuf,
1162 macho_segcmdsize +
1163 macho_sectcmdsize * objfmt_macho->parse_scnum);
1164 /* in an MH_OBJECT file all sections are in one unnamed (name all zeros)
1165 * segment (16x0)
1166 */
1167 YASM_WRITE_32_L(localbuf, 0);
1168 YASM_WRITE_32_L(localbuf, 0);
1169 YASM_WRITE_32_L(localbuf, 0);
1170 YASM_WRITE_32_L(localbuf, 0);
1171
1172 /* in-memory offset, in-memory size */
1173 yasm_intnum_set_uint(val, 0); /* offset in memory (vmaddr) */
1174 yasm_intnum_get_sized(val, localbuf, long_int_bytes,
1175 ((long_int_bytes) << 3), 0, 0, 0);
1176 localbuf += long_int_bytes;
1177 yasm_intnum_set_uint(val, info.vmsize); /* size in memory (vmsize) */
1178 yasm_intnum_get_sized(val, localbuf, long_int_bytes,
1179 ((long_int_bytes) << 3), 0, 0, 0);
1180 localbuf += long_int_bytes;
1181 /* offset in file to first section */
1182 yasm_intnum_set_uint(val, fileoffset);
1183 yasm_intnum_get_sized(val, localbuf, long_int_bytes,
1184 ((long_int_bytes) << 3), 0, 0, 0);
1185 localbuf += long_int_bytes;
1186 yasm_intnum_set_uint(val, info.filesize); /* overall size in file */
1187 yasm_intnum_get_sized(val, localbuf, long_int_bytes,
1188 ((long_int_bytes) << 3), 0, 0, 0);
1189 localbuf += long_int_bytes;
1190
1191 YASM_WRITE_32_L(localbuf, VM_PROT_DEFAULT); /* VM protection, maximum */
1192 YASM_WRITE_32_L(localbuf, VM_PROT_DEFAULT); /* VM protection, initial */
1193 /* number of sections */
1194 YASM_WRITE_32_L(localbuf, objfmt_macho->parse_scnum);
1195 YASM_WRITE_32_L(localbuf, 0); /* no flags */
1196
1197 /* write MACH-O header and segment command to outfile */
1198 fwrite(info.buf, (size_t) (localbuf - info.buf), 1, f);
1199
1200 /* next: section headers */
1201 /* offset to relocs for first section */
1202 info.rel_base = align32((long)fileoff_sections);
1203 info.s_reloff = 0; /* offset for relocs of following sections */
1204 yasm_object_sections_traverse(object, &info, macho_objfmt_output_secthead);
1205
1206 localbuf = info.buf;
1207 /* write out symbol command */
1208 YASM_WRITE_32_L(localbuf, LC_SYMTAB); /* cmd == LC_SYMTAB */
1209 YASM_WRITE_32_L(localbuf, MACHO_SYMCMD_SIZE);
1210 /* symbol table offset */
1211 YASM_WRITE_32_L(localbuf, info.rel_base + info.s_reloff);
1212 YASM_WRITE_32_L(localbuf, symtab_count); /* number of symbols */
1213
1214 YASM_WRITE_32_L(localbuf, macho_nlistsize * symtab_count + info.rel_base +
1215 info.s_reloff); /* string table offset */
1216 YASM_WRITE_32_L(localbuf, info.strlength); /* string table size */
1217 /* write symbol command */
1218 fwrite(info.buf, (size_t)(localbuf - info.buf), 1, f);
1219
1220 /*printf("num symbols %d, vmsize %d, filesize %d\n",symtab_count,
1221 info.vmsize, info.filesize ); */
1222
1223 /* get back to end of raw section data */
1224 if (fseek(f, (long)fileoff_sections, SEEK_SET) < 0) {
1225 yasm__fatal(N_("could not seek on output file"));
1226 /*@notreached@*/
1227 return;
1228 }
1229
1230 /* padding to long boundary */
1231 if ((info.rel_base - fileoff_sections) > 0) {
1232 fwrite(pad_data, info.rel_base - fileoff_sections, 1, f);
1233 }
1234
1235 /* relocation data */
1236 yasm_object_sections_traverse(object, &info, macho_objfmt_output_relocs);
1237
1238 /* symbol table (NLIST) */
1239 info.indx = 1; /* restart symbol table indices */
1240 yasm_symtab_traverse(object->symtab, &info, macho_objfmt_output_symtable);
1241
1242 /* symbol strings */
1243 fwrite(pad_data, 1, 1, f);
1244 yasm_symtab_traverse(object->symtab, &info, macho_objfmt_output_str);
1245
1246 yasm_intnum_destroy(val);
1247 yasm_xfree(info.buf);
1248}

1258{

1262 macho_section_data *data;

1386 struct macho_section_switch_data {
1387 /*@only@*/ /*@null@*/ char *f_segname;
1388 /*@only@*/ /*@null@*/ yasm_intnum *align_intn;
1389 } data;
1390
1391 static const yasm_dir_help help[] = {
1392 { "segname", 1, yasm_dir_helper_string,
1393 offsetof(struct macho_section_switch_data, f_segname), 0 },
1394 { "align", 1, yasm_dir_helper_intn,
1395 offsetof(struct macho_section_switch_data, align_intn), 0 }
1396 };
1397
1398 data.f_segname = NULL;
1399 data.align_intn = NULL;
1400
1401 vp = yasm_vps_first(valparams);
1402 sectname = yasm_vp_string(vp);
1403 if (!sectname)
1404 return NULL;
1405 vp = yasm_vps_next(vp);
1406
1407 /* translate .text,.data,.bss to __text,__data,__bss... */
1408 for (i=0; i<NELEMS(section_name_translation); i++) {
1409 if (yasm__strcasecmp(sectname, section_name_translation[i].in) == 0)
1410 break;
1411 }
1412
1413 if (i == NELEMS(section_name_translation)) {
1414 const char *s;
1415 if (vp && !vp->val && (s = yasm_vp_string(vp))) {
1416 /* Treat as SEGNAME, SECTNAME */
1417 if (strlen(sectname) > 16)
1418 yasm_warn_set(YASM_WARN_GENERAL,
1419 N_("segment name is too long, max 16 chars; truncating"));
1420 data.f_segname = yasm__xstrndup(sectname, 16);
1421 if (strlen(s) > 16)
1422 yasm_warn_set(YASM_WARN_GENERAL,
1423 N_("section name is too long, max 16 chars; truncating"));
1424 f_sectname = yasm__xstrndup(s, 16);
1425 flags = S_REGULAR;
1426 align = 0;
1427
1428 sectname = s;
1429 vp = yasm_vps_next(vp);
1430 } else {
1431 data.f_segname = NULL;
1432 if (strlen(sectname) > 16)
1433 yasm_warn_set(YASM_WARN_GENERAL,
1434 N_("section name is too long, max 16 chars; truncating"));
1435 f_sectname = yasm__xstrndup(sectname, 16);
1436 flags = S_ATTR_SOME_INSTRUCTIONS;
1437 align = 0;
1438 }
1439 } else {
1440 data.f_segname = yasm__xstrdup(section_name_translation[i].seg);
1441 f_sectname = yasm__xstrdup(section_name_translation[i].sect);
1442 flags = section_name_translation[i].flags;
1443 align = section_name_translation[i].align;
1444 }
1445
1446 flags_override = yasm_dir_helper(object, vp, line, help, NELEMS(help),
1447 &data, yasm_dir_helper_valparam_warn);
1448 if (flags_override < 0)
1449 return NULL; /* error occurred */
1450
1451 if (data.align_intn) {
1452 align = yasm_intnum_get_uint(data.align_intn);
1453 yasm_intnum_destroy(data.align_intn);
1454
1455 /* Alignments must be a power of two. */
1456 if (!is_exp2(align)) {
1457 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_VALUE,
1458 N_("argument to `%s' is not a power of two"),
1459 vp->val);
1460 return NULL;
1461 }
1462
1463 /* Check to see if alignment is supported size */
1464 if (align > 16384) {
1465 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_VALUE,
1466 N_("macho implementation does not support alignments > 16384"));
1467 return NULL;
1468 }
1469 }
1470
1471 if (!data.f_segname) {
1472 yasm_warn_set(YASM_WARN_GENERAL,
1473 N_("Unknown section name, defaulting to __TEXT segment"));
1474 data.f_segname = yasm__xstrdup("__TEXT");
1475 }
1476
1477 /* Build a unique sectname from f_segname and f_sectname. */
1478 realname = yasm_xmalloc(strlen("LC_SEGMENT") + 1 + strlen(data.f_segname) + 1 +
1479 strlen(f_sectname) + 1);
1480 sprintf(realname, "LC_SEGMENT.%s.%s", data.f_segname, f_sectname);
1481 retval = yasm_object_get_general(object, realname, align, 1, resonly,
1482 &isnew, line);
1483 yasm_xfree(realname);
1484
1485 msd = yasm_section_get_data(retval, &macho_section_data_cb);
1486
1487 if (isnew || yasm_section_is_default(retval)) {
1488 yasm_section_set_default(retval, 0);
1489 msd->segname = data.f_segname;
1490 msd->sectname = f_sectname;
1491 msd->flags = flags;
1492 yasm_section_set_align(retval, align, line);
1493 } else if (flags_override) {
1494 /* align is the only value used from overrides. */
1495 if (yasm_section_get_align(retval) != align) {
1496 yasm_warn_set(YASM_WARN_GENERAL,
1497 N_("section flags ignored on section redeclaration"));
1498 }
1499 }
1500 return retval;
1501}
